Anzac Day is the only day of the year when two-up is legal in Australia  . 
  The game dates back to Australia's goldfields and is illegal at all other times  . 
  On Saturday Aussies commemorated the centenary of the landing at Gallipoli  . 
  Thousands of people played the coin game in pubs and clubs all around the country . 
  The game is legal on Anzac Day across Returned Servicemen League clubs . 
 